<Link id="l02201" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2201"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// here. Instead the following loop consumes the register defs in an</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02202" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2202"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// arbitrary order. At least it handles the common case of clustered loads</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02203" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2203"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// to the same class. For precise liveness, each SDep needs to indicate the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02204" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2204"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// result number. But that tightly couples the ScheduleDAG with the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02205" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2205"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// SelectionDAG making updates tricky. A simpler hack would be to attach a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02206" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2206"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// value type or register class to SDep.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02207" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2207"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02208" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2208"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The most important aspect of register tracking is balancing the increase</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02209" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2209"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// here with the reduction further below. Note that this SU may use multiple</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02210" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2210"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// defs in PredSU. The can&#39;t be determined here, but we&#39;ve already</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02597" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2597"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// t2 = op c3</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02600" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2600"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Then schedule t2 = op first.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02601" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2601"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// i.e.</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02925" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2925"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02926" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2926"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// PrescheduleNodesWithMultipleUses - Nodes with multiple uses</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02927" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2927"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// are not handled well by the general register pressure reduction</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02928" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2928"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// heuristics. When presented with code like this:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02929" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2929"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02930" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2930"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///      N</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02931" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2931"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    / |</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02932" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2932"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   /  |</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02933" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2933"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///  U  store</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02934" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2934"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///  |</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02935" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2935"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// ...</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02936" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2936"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02937" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2937"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// the heuristics tend to push the store up, but since the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02938" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2938"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// operand of the store has another use (U), this would increase</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02939" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2939"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// the length of that other use (the U-&gt;N edge).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02940" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2940"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02941" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2941"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// This function transforms code like the above to route U&#39;s</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02942" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2942"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// dependence through the store when possible, like this:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02943" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2943"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02944" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2944"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///      N</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02945" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2945"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///      ||</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02946" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2946"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///      ||</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02947" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2947"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     store</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02948" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2948"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///       |</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02949" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2949"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///       U</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02950" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2950"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///       |</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02951" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2951"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///      ...</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02952" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2952"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02953" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2953"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// This results in the store being scheduled immediately</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02954" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2954"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// after N, which shortens the U-&gt;N live range, reducing</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02955" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2955"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// register pressure.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02956" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2956" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/anonymous-namespace-scheduledagrrlist-cpp-/regreductionpqbase/#a6df9e18cc58cb146ccfa7c7d47b6b9ca"><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">void</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/anonymous-namespace-scheduledagrrlist-cpp-/regreductionpqbase/#a6df9e18cc58cb146ccfa7c7d47b6b9ca">RegReductionPQBase::PrescheduleNodesWithMultipleUses</a>() &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02957" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2957"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Visit all the nodes in topological order, working top-down.</span></CodeLine>
